access: The whole house except our bedroom.
additional_house_rules:
Our home is a smoke-and-shoe-free environment.
Please clean up after yourself.
description:
Our cute and comfortable apartment is situated in the heart of Williamsburg, a very charming and artistic area. It is well connected with buses and trains (J-M-Z-L-G) and there are lots of options for food, bars (many overlooking Manhattan on rooftops) and clubs.
Besides the private bedroom, our living room sofa bed is available as well.

Very comfortable house with a spiderweb relaxing chair and a minibar in the living room. You have full use of the kitchen.
The bedrooms has a Queen bed, a night stand, a desk, and a huge closet.
Our guests can stay in a bedroom (up to 2 guests) and the living room, where we have a big sofa bed (up to 2 guests, with additional cost).

The whole house except our bedroom.

I am Italian and my wife is Korean. We are very nice and welcoming and enjoy meeting people of all cultures. We speak English, Italian, Korean, Spanish, and a sprinkling of French. We are open to spending time with our guests but it's also fine if you want to do your own thing. We can give recommendations to places to see and eat and are available for any questions you may have.

Our neighborhood is super cool; lots and lots of things to do!!!
Restaurants, bars, clubs, art events, flea markets, parks. Let me know what you are interested in and I will try my best to guide you. 
Super safe and nice area, very well connected.

It is super easy get from the JFK airport to our house with one train (J or Z). The J-M-Z trains are a 2 minutes walk from the house and the L train is a 12 minute walk. In addition, the G train is 10 minutes away. There is a major bus station in front of the house.
The subways are connected to Manhattan, with Lower East Side being 1 stop away.

hosts.about:
Hi I'm Valerio
I am an Italian guy from Rome.
I came to New York about 3 years ago and I fell in love with my amazing Korean wife Kiki.
I love everything about food, from how it grows to how it can be transformed to different ways to eat it. People say I cook very well when I invite them over; that's why I hope maybe one day when you are my guest, I can let you try something.
I love to travel with my wife and try different kinds of food and meet different kind of people and culture. I think is amazing and make people rich inside.
I think time is the most beautiful and priceless gift you can give to someone because it will never come back.
